'''Konrad Laimer''' (born 27 May 1997) is an Austrian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]], [[left-back]] or [[midfielder]] for {{German football updater|BaMunich}} club [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Cite web|title=K. Laimer|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/konrad-laimer/316760/|website=Soccerway|access-date=24 December 2014}}</ref> He was selected as [[Austrian Footballer of the Year]] in 2025.

==Club career==
===Red Bull Salzburg===
A youth product of [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]], Laimer made his [[Austrian Football First League|Erste Liga]] debut with the reserve team and feeder club [[FC Liefering]] on 2 May 2014 against [[SV Horn]].<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|title=Horn vs. Liefering|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/05/02/austria/1-liga/sv-horn/usk-anif/1487664/|website=Soccerway|date=2 May 2014|access-date=24 December 2014}}</ref> He made his first team debut at 28 September 2014 against [[SK Rapid Wien|Rapid Wien]]. He replaced [[Alan Carvalho|Alan]] in added time.<ref name="soccerway3">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/09/28/austria/bundesliga/sk-rapid-wien/fc-red-bull-salzburg/1692413/|title=Rapid Wien vs. Salzburg|date=28 September 2014|website=Soccerway|access-date=24 December 2014}}</ref>

===RB Leipzig===
On 30 June 2017, Laimer moved to Germany and joined [[RB Leipzig]] on a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Transfermeldung: Konrad Laimer wechselt zu RB Leipzig!|url=http://www.dierotenbullen.com/de/aktuelles/neuigkeiten/Saison_2016_17/Neuzugang-Konrad-Laimer.html|website=RB Leipzig|date=15 September 2023 |language=de}}</ref> He scored his first [[Bundesliga]] goal in a 4–0 away win over [[Fortuna Düsseldorf]] on 27 January 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/517727/rb-leipzig-fortuna-dusseldorf |title=Fortuna Düsseldorf 0–4 RB Leipzig |publisher=ESPN |date=27 January 2019 }}</ref> Later that year, on 23 October, he netted his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in a 2–1 victory over [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/557121/zenit-st-petersburg-rb-leipzig |title=RB Leipzig 2–1 Zenit St Petersburg |publisher=ESPN |date=23 October 2019 }}</ref>

Laimer's deal was due to run out in 2021, but he later signed a contract extension until June 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Konrad Laimer verlängert seinen Vertrag bis 2023|url=https://rbleipzig.com/de/news/2019-2020/konrad-laimer-verlaengert-seinen-vetrag-bis-2023/|website=RB Leipzig|date=18 February 2020|language=de|access-date=9 May 2022|archive-date=31 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220531020901/https://rbleipzig.com/de/news/2019-2020/konrad-laimer-verlaengert-seinen-vetrag-bis-2023/|url-status=dead}}</ref> He won the [[DFB-Pokal]] in [[2022 DFB-Pokal final|2022]] and [[2023 DFB-Pokal final|2023]] with Leipzig.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Manuel|last=Veth|title=RB Leipzig: DFB Pokal Victory The End And Start Of An Era|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/manuelveth/2023/06/04/rb-leipzig-dfb-pokal-victory-the-end-and-start-of-an-era/|website=[[Forbes]]|access-date=9 June 2023}}</ref> On 3 June 2023, despite their victory in the 2023 DFB-Pokal, Laimer announced his decision to depart from RB Leipzig.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Bundesliga: Konrad Laimer confirms RB Leipzig exit ahead of expected move to Bayern Munich|url=https://uk.news.yahoo.com/bundesliga-konrad-laimer-confirms-rb-095900148.html|website=Yahoo News|date=5 June 2023|access-date=9 June 2023}}</ref>

===Bayern Munich===
[[File:FC Red Bull Salzburg gegen Bayern München (2025-01-06 Testspiel) 15.jpg|thumb|upright=0.85|Laimer warming up for [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in 2025]]

On 9 June 2023, Bayern Munich announced that they had signed Laimer on a free transfer until 30 June 2027.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Konrad Laimer joins Bayern on contract till 2027|url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/06/konrad-laimer-joins-bayern-on-contract-till-2027|website=FC Bayern Munich|date=9 June 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Bayern Munich sign Konrad Laimer from RB Leipzig |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayern-munich-sign-konrad-laimer-from-rb-leipzig-23736|website=FC Bayern Munich|access-date=9 June 2023}}</ref> On 8 August 2023, Laimer changed his shirt number at Bayern from 24 to his favorite number, 27. The number had become vacant with previous owner [[Yann Sommer]]'s departure from the club.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Konrad Laimer chooses new squad number|url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/08/change-of-jersey---konrad-laimer-chooses-new-squad-number|website=FC Bayern Munich|date=8 August 2023}}</ref> On 26 September, he scored his first goal for Bayern in a 4–0 away win over [[SC Preußen Münster|Preußen Münster]] in the [[2023–24 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 September 2023 |title=Bayern through to DFB Cup second |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/matches/profis/dfb-pokal/2023-2024/sc-preussen-muenster-fc-bayern-muenchen-25-09-2023/reportround |website=FC Bayern Munich}}</ref> On 10 December 2024, he netted his first Champions League goal with Bayern in a 5–1 away win over [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/matches/profis/champions-league/2024-2025/schachtar-donezk-fc-bayern-muenchen-10-12-2024/report |title=Bayern claim vital win over Shakhtar |website=FC Bayern Munich |date=10 December 2024 }}</ref> Laimer won his first title with Bayern Munich in the [[2024–25 Bundesliga]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/news/2025/05/diese-fc-bayern-spieler-feiern-ihre-erste-deutsche-meisterschaft |title=Diese FC Bayern-Spieler feiern ihre erste Deutsche Meisterschaft |website=FC Bayern Munich |language=de |date=4 May 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
In September 2017, Laimer received his first call-up to the [[Austria national football team|Austrian senior squad]] for [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches against [[Wales national football team|Wales]] and [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] in September 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Wales vs. Austria|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/wales-vs-austria-tv-channel-free-stream-kick-off-time-odds-match-/19qhpl544djsw1tis3qf2vh2gw|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal.com]]|date=2 September 2017|access-date=4 September 2017}}</ref> On 7 June 2019, he debuted as a starter in a [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying Group G|UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]] against [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=National Team Debüt von Konrad Laimer: Überfällig und abgebrüht|trans-title=Konrad Laimer's national team debut: long overdue and hardened|url=https://www.laola1.at/de/red/fussball/oefb-nationalteam/a-team/news/nationalteam-debuet-von-konrad-laimer--ueberfaellig-und-abgebrueht/|website=[[Laola1]]|date=8 June 2019|language=de}}</ref>

